fields.description:
כמשתמש אוכל להגיע למסך עדכונים מהשטח על-ידי לחיצה על כפתור ממסך עוד.
כמשתמש אוכל לראות את הפיד של עדכונים מהשטח שפורסמו על-ידי משתמשים אחרים באפליקציה.

כמשתמש בכל דיווח שפורסם אוכל לראות תמונה במידה ויש, להיכנס אליה ולראות אותה במסך מלא, לחיצה נוספת תחזיר אותי לפיד. אוכל לראות גם מתי פורסם הדיווח - לפני ד'ות/שעות ימים/שבועות/חודשים לחיצה על התגובות תוביל אותי למסך התגובות של הדיווח, במסך זה אוכל להוסיף תגובה במידה וארצה על-ידי כפתור +.

fields.description:
As a user I will be able to see the header
1.	By tapping on the "Back" button user will be able to go back to the page he came from 
1.1	On the first page of the session flow the "back" button will be replaced with a "close" button 
1.2	By tapping on the close button user will be able to close session flow
2.	By tapping on the "next" button user will be able to go to the next part of the session flow 
2.1.	In the last session flow page the next button will be change to an "end" button
2.2.	The Next/End button will be clickable only after the user have chose an answer
3.	By tapping on the next button the answer is saved as long as the user is continuing on the flow (meaning - if he goes back he will see the answers he checked)
4.	Only by tapping on the "END" button the users answers are saved as a full session and the information is calculated   
4.1.	by tapping the "End" button user will go to the "My Last session page"

fields.description:
As a user I will be able to see a graph summarizing the data of a specific question 

As a user I will be able to see the description of a specific dot

(The inner state graph is described apart from the other graphs)
The graphs themselves are already developed - the new part is what happens once you tap on a dot 
1.	once tapping on a specific dot on the graphs user will see the specific information the dote represents -  
1.1.	The relevant illustration, the name variable (body, presence, mind, etc.), the user's answer in the specific session and the relevant percentage 
1.2.	The date and time of the session
1.3. by tapping the "close" button user will go back to the graph he came from

fields.description:
As a user I will be able to see the progress bar
1. The progress bar will be visible in the "your session" flow
2. The progress bar will show the user how much more steps he needs to take in order for him to complete a session (Progress bar will have 8 points in it)
3. The progress bar will change according to the page the user is standing in (meaning \- if the user will go back the progress bar will change accordingly)

4.The progress bar won't change in the last optional question \- "was this special evet"
